{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/110800", "id": 1327270170, "node_id": "PR_kwDOAAsO6M5PHIka", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/110800", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/110800.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/110800.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/110800", "number": 110800, "state": "open", "locked": false, "title": "Accept additional user-defined classes in fenced code blocks", "user": {"login": "GuillaumeGomez", "id": 3050060, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMwNTAwNjA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3050060?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez", "html_url": "https://github.com/GuillaumeGomez", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Part of #79483.\r\n\r\nThis is a re-opening of https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/79454 after a big update/cleanup. I also converted the syntax to pandoc as suggested by @notriddle: the idea is to be as compatible as possible with the existing instead of having our own syntax.\r\n\r\nThis allow users to write the following:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n/// Some code block with `rust,{class=test}` as the language string\r\n///\r\n/// {class=test}\r\n/// int main(void) {\r\n///     return 0;\r\n/// }\r\n/// ```\r\nfn main() {}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis will notably produce the following HTML:\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<pre class=\"test\">\r\nint main(void) {\r\n    return 0;\r\n}</pre>\r\n```\r\n\r\nInstead of:\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<pre class=\"rust rust-example-rendered\">\r\n<span class=\"ident\">int</span> <span class=\"ident\">main</span>(<span class=\"ident\">void</span>) {\r\n    <span class=\"kw\">return</span> <span class=\"number\">0</span>;\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo be noted, we could have written `{.test}` to achieve the same result. `.` and `class=` have the same effect.\r\n\r\nOne last syntax point: content between parens (`(like this)`) is now considered as comment and is not taken into account at all.\r\n\r\nIn addition to this, I added an `unknown` field into `LangString` (the parsed code block \"attribute\") because of cases like this:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n/// ```{class=language-c}\r\n/// main;\r\n/// ```\r\npub fn foo() {}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWithout this `unknown` field, it would generate in the DOM: `<pre class=\"language-class:language-c language-c\">`, which is quite bad. So instead, it now stores all unknown tags into the `unknown` field and use the first one as \"language\". So in this case, since there is no unknown tag, it'll simply generate `<pre class=\"language-c\">`. I added tests to cover this.\r\n\r\nFinally, I added a parser for the codeblock attributes to make it much easier to maintain. It'll be pretty easy to extend.\r\n\r\ncc @poliorcetics\r\nr? @notriddle ", "created_at": "2023-04-25T14:46:57Z", "updated_at": "2023-05-30T21:48:46Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "db1d391dc3fca063b76a965bece7f25dd96d6acf", "assignee": {"login": "notriddle", "id": 1593513, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE1OTM1MTM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1593513?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/notriddle", "html_url": "https://github.com/notriddle", "followers